# Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

We pledge to make participation in this project a respectful and welcoming experience for everyone. We are committed to creating an open environment where all contributors feel safe, valued, and included.

## Our Standards

Examples of positive behavior include:

- Using respectful and welcoming language
- Being kind to other contributors
- Accepting constructive feedback
- Respecting different opinions and experiences
- Helping others when possible

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

- Harassment, insults, or offensive comments
- Personal attacks
- Discrimination of any kind
- Sharing private information without permission
- Any behavior that makes others feel unsafe or unwelcome

## Enforcement Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for explaining and enforcing this Code of Conduct. They may remove comments, commits, issues, or contributions that do not follow these standards.

## Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all project spaces, including the GitHub repository, issues, pull requests, discussions, and any related communication about the project.

## Enforcement

Instances of unacceptable behavior may be reported to the project maintainers. The maintainers will review the issue and take appropriate action fairly and respectfully.

## Enforcement Guidelines

Maintainers may take the following actions depending on the situation:

1. Warning the person involved
2. Removing inappropriate content
3. Temporarily limiting participation
4. Permanently banning someone from participating in the project

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is inspired by common open-source community guidelines and the Contributor Covenant.
